1
00:01:54,590 --> 00:01:57,350
Why do we have to move?

2
00:01:58,509 --> 00:02:00,840
Where are we even going?

3
00:02:02,150 --> 00:02:04,790
We'll never come back.

4
00:02:05,430 --> 00:02:07,400
Miaomiao, why are you all crying here?

5
00:02:07,400 --> 00:02:08,710
Stop getting in the way.

6
00:02:08,710 --> 00:02:09,680
We won't leave!

7
00:02:09,680 --> 00:02:11,280
No one can separate us!

8
00:02:11,430 --> 00:02:13,630
Yes, we're staying!

9
00:02:13,630 --> 00:02:15,890
Who said anything about separating you?

10
00:02:15,960 --> 00:02:16,800
We're all moving together.

11
00:02:16,800 --> 00:02:18,030
To a new base.

12
00:02:19,800 --> 00:02:20,430
Let's go.

13
00:02:22,710 --> 00:02:24,630
Come on, Mom already said

14
00:02:24,630 --> 00:02:26,290
that we'd never be separated.

15
00:03:01,840 --> 00:03:03,870
Take Li Si for treatment as soon as possible.

16
00:03:03,870 --> 00:03:05,200
Don't delay any longer.

17
00:03:32,079 --> 00:03:33,030
You startled me.

18
00:03:33,630 --> 00:03:34,710
Why are you here?

19
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:36,120
I just called you.

20
00:03:36,120 --> 00:03:37,380
Why didn't you answer?

21
00:03:41,520 --> 00:03:42,560
What's wrong?

22
00:03:53,310 --> 00:03:54,840
People are watching.

23
00:03:55,310 --> 00:03:57,190
It's okay. I'm here.

24
00:04:00,430 --> 00:04:01,560
I'm telling you all.

25
00:04:02,190 --> 00:04:03,920
From now on, when you talk to me,

26
00:04:03,920 --> 00:04:05,590
you've got to be more careful.

27
00:04:06,120 --> 00:04:08,710
Fang is going to be my uncle's wife.

28
00:04:08,710 --> 00:04:09,590
Wait.

29
00:04:09,590 --> 00:04:10,750
Why is Fang

30
00:04:10,750 --> 00:04:12,230
dating your uncle now?

31
00:04:12,430 --> 00:04:12,910
Didn't she

32
00:04:12,910 --> 00:04:13,840
hit it off

33
00:04:13,840 --> 00:04:15,430
with Cheng Miaomiao's uncle?

34
00:04:15,430 --> 00:04:16,230
Zhu Chao!

35
00:04:17,160 --> 00:04:18,040
Do you still

36
00:04:18,040 --> 00:04:19,800
want to be the Class Monitor next semester?

37
00:04:19,800 --> 00:04:21,000
If you do,

38
00:04:22,200 --> 00:04:23,930
a word from me will do the trick!

39
00:04:24,510 --> 00:04:25,270
Li Si!

40
00:04:27,920 --> 00:04:29,380
You've got long legs, huh?

41
00:04:29,680 --> 00:04:30,430
There isn't enough space to put them,

42
00:04:30,430 --> 00:04:32,240
so you put them on the table, right?

43
00:04:32,240 --> 00:04:33,000
Good.

44
00:04:33,120 --> 00:04:34,270
Let's put your long legs to good use.

45
00:04:34,270 --> 00:04:35,390
Go mop the floor.

46
00:04:40,920 --> 00:04:42,270
Why are you mopping the floor?

47
00:04:42,270 --> 00:04:43,070
What did you do this time?

48
00:04:43,070 --> 00:04:44,530
Can't you behave for once?

49
00:04:44,920 --> 00:04:46,070
How can you say that?

50
00:04:46,360 --> 00:04:47,800
I'm doing this

51
00:04:47,800 --> 00:04:49,870
purely out of love for the school.

52
00:04:49,870 --> 00:04:50,480
Go on and mop.

53
00:04:50,480 --> 00:04:52,080
Just think of it as exercise.

54
00:04:58,510 --> 00:04:59,240
Pengfei.

55
00:05:01,950 --> 00:05:03,080
T-T-This is Dr. Liu.

56
00:05:03,160 --> 00:05:04,160
Are the results out?

57
00:05:04,160 --> 00:05:04,920
Y-Y-You... well...

58
00:05:04,920 --> 00:05:06,070
Have a seat first. Sit.

59
00:05:06,070 --> 00:05:06,800
Take a seat.

60
00:05:06,800 --> 00:05:08,110
I'll ask him.

61
00:05:08,750 --> 00:05:09,750
-Dr. Liu.
-Dr. Liu

62
00:05:09,750 --> 00:05:11,080
Dr. Liu, please tell me.

63
00:05:12,430 --> 00:05:13,240
How is it?

64
00:05:25,160 --> 00:05:26,560
Does he have colon cancer?

65
00:05:26,560 --> 00:05:28,820
Yes, it's confirmed. It's colon cancer.

66
00:05:35,040 --> 00:05:37,480
The medical resources at our oilfield hospital are limited.

67
00:05:37,480 --> 00:05:38,270
I suggest

68
00:05:38,270 --> 00:05:41,330
you take him to a hospital in a larger city immediately.

69
00:05:57,800 --> 00:05:58,659
Beijing, then?

70
00:06:00,040 --> 00:06:00,950
The cost of cancer treatment

71
00:06:00,950 --> 00:06:02,040
is still quite high.

72
00:06:02,040 --> 00:06:03,800
You need to be mentally prepared.

73
00:06:03,800 --> 00:06:06,720
What are the chances of a cure...

74
00:06:07,070 --> 00:06:09,430
after the surgery?

75
00:06:13,000 --> 00:06:14,310
Colon cancer...

76
00:06:14,430 --> 00:06:15,560
is quite special.

77
00:06:15,950 --> 00:06:18,120
Before detection, there are typically no symptoms.

78
00:06:18,120 --> 00:06:19,920
However, once it is discovered,

79
00:06:20,390 --> 00:06:22,720
the outlook is often not very optimistic.

80
00:06:25,920 --> 00:06:27,240
Based on my assessment,

81
00:06:27,240 --> 00:06:29,240
the chance of surgery curing it is already very low.

82
00:06:29,240 --> 00:06:31,000
It's already in an advanced stage.

83
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:31,920
The only remaining option

84
00:06:31,920 --> 00:06:33,520
is conservative treatment.

85
00:06:34,430 --> 00:06:35,240
But even that

86
00:06:35,360 --> 00:06:36,830
will only slightly

87
00:06:37,270 --> 00:06:39,200
extend his life for a short period.

88
00:06:41,190 --> 00:06:42,120
How long?

89
00:06:44,360 --> 00:06:46,560
About... three to six months.

90
00:07:19,600 --> 00:07:20,390
Mom?

91
00:07:21,830 --> 00:07:22,630
Mom!

92
00:07:23,760 --> 00:07:24,720
Mom!

93
00:07:26,830 --> 00:07:27,800
Son, you're back.

94
00:07:27,800 --> 00:07:28,730
What's going on?

95
00:07:29,430 --> 00:07:30,070
Why did my dad

96
00:07:30,070 --> 00:07:31,160
come back so early today?

97
00:07:31,160 --> 00:07:32,420
And he's even cooking.

98
00:07:33,000 --> 00:07:34,800
Your dad didn't have much to do at work today,

99
00:07:34,800 --> 00:07:36,000
so he came back early.

100
00:07:36,270 --> 00:07:37,070
You're back.

101
00:07:38,510 --> 00:07:39,120
You...

102
00:07:39,120 --> 00:07:40,390
You're back, son?

103
00:07:41,800 --> 00:07:44,000
Wash your hands, and let's have dinner.

104
00:07:45,870 --> 00:07:46,670
What's wrong?

105
00:07:47,720 --> 00:07:48,920
Nothing.

106
00:07:49,600 --> 00:07:50,600
Did you two fight?

107
00:07:51,190 --> 00:07:52,270
No, I...

108
00:07:54,190 --> 00:07:54,920
No. No.

109
00:07:56,630 --> 00:07:58,360
Something must have happened.

110
00:07:58,360 --> 00:07:59,480
Something big must have happened.

111
00:07:59,480 --> 00:08:01,000
What nonsense are you talking about?

112
00:08:01,000 --> 00:08:02,680
What big thing could've happened?

113
00:08:02,680 --> 00:08:03,600
Hurry up.

114
00:08:03,680 --> 00:08:04,600
Wash your hands, and let's have dinner.

115
00:08:04,600 --> 00:08:06,390
Be good. Try your dad's cooking.

116
00:08:06,390 --> 00:08:07,120
Wait...

117
00:08:07,120 --> 00:08:07,800
Go, son.

118
00:08:07,800 --> 00:08:08,560
Mom!

119
00:08:08,560 --> 00:08:09,720
Go. Go.

120
00:08:09,830 --> 00:08:11,360
Hurry. Be good.

121
00:08:32,080 --> 00:08:33,140
Don't tell the kids

122
00:08:34,150 --> 00:08:35,360
about this.

123
00:08:36,440 --> 00:08:38,770
I'm afraid they won't be able to handle it.

124
00:08:40,270 --> 00:08:41,440
I'll go... go check on Ling.

125
00:08:41,440 --> 00:08:42,750
No, no, don't go.

126
00:08:44,320 --> 00:08:46,120
What will you say to her if you go?

127
00:08:49,870 --> 00:08:51,200
Well...

128
00:08:52,120 --> 00:08:53,780
Could this be a misdiagnosis?

129
00:08:54,320 --> 00:08:55,390
The biopsy

130
00:08:55,840 --> 00:08:56,630
is currently

131
00:08:57,000 --> 00:08:57,870
the most accurate and direct method

132
00:08:57,870 --> 00:08:59,840
for diagnosing colon cancer.

133
00:09:02,270 --> 00:09:04,000
But what is Ling supposed to do?

134
00:09:04,000 --> 00:09:05,320
How can she face it?

135
00:09:07,030 --> 00:09:08,600
Mom, I'm back!

136
00:09:15,150 --> 00:09:16,390
You're back so early.

137
00:09:20,910 --> 00:09:21,760
Come on, son.

138
00:09:22,910 --> 00:09:24,150
This fish is so fresh.

139
00:09:24,150 --> 00:09:24,630
Someone caught it,

140
00:09:24,630 --> 00:09:25,960
and I bought it halfway.

141
00:09:26,360 --> 00:09:27,320
Try my cooking.

142
00:09:27,320 --> 00:09:28,480
I haven't cooked in a long time.

143
00:09:28,480 --> 00:09:31,340
I don't know if my cooking skills are still up to par.

144
00:09:31,550 --> 00:09:31,720
Come on. Come on.

145
00:09:31,720 --> 00:09:33,320
Let me pour you a drink. Here.

146
00:09:37,360 --> 00:09:38,960
Did you make some mistakes?

147
00:09:40,550 --> 00:09:42,150
What mistakes could I have made?

148
00:09:42,150 --> 00:09:43,550
Bai Shuang is here again?

149
00:09:44,550 --> 00:09:45,840
Son, your dad would never

150
00:09:45,840 --> 00:09:47,440
make that kind of mistake.

151
00:09:47,440 --> 00:09:48,670
There's nothing like that going on.

152
00:09:48,670 --> 00:09:49,270
So you must have done something

153
00:09:49,270 --> 00:09:50,670
to upset me then.

154
00:09:51,320 --> 00:09:52,120
Mom,

155
00:09:53,790 --> 00:09:55,850
you two are hiding something from me.

156
00:10:03,270 --> 00:10:04,030
Are you two getting a divorce?

157
00:10:04,030 --> 00:10:05,360
Then, who will I be with?

158
00:10:07,040 --> 00:10:07,840
Silly boy.

159
00:10:08,910 --> 00:10:10,150
Your dad and I will not be getting a divorce.

160
00:10:10,150 --> 00:10:11,480
How could we divorce?

161
00:10:14,870 --> 00:10:16,070
It's okay if she doesn't want to eat it.

162
00:10:16,070 --> 00:10:16,910
Just leave it there.

163
00:10:16,910 --> 00:10:18,270
You eat up.

164
00:10:18,720 --> 00:10:19,750
I've noticed

165
00:10:19,750 --> 00:10:21,750
that Director Xiao's dressing style has changed recently.

166
00:10:21,750 --> 00:10:23,320
Have you seen her hair today?

167
00:10:23,320 --> 00:10:24,320
Those little curls she has.

168
00:10:24,320 --> 00:10:26,270
She's even starting to go for a softer look.

169
00:10:26,270 --> 00:10:28,230
I-I-It's all just a facade.

170
00:10:28,790 --> 00:10:29,750
This afternoon,

171
00:10:30,080 --> 00:10:31,870
she scolded Li Si

172
00:10:31,870 --> 00:10:32,600
and made him

173
00:10:32,600 --> 00:10:33,960
mop the entire hallway.

174
00:10:34,360 --> 00:10:35,870
But honestly, Li Si had it coming.

175
00:10:35,870 --> 00:10:36,910
He kept bragging everywhere

176
00:10:36,910 --> 00:10:38,960
that Fang was his aunt.

177
00:10:39,120 --> 00:10:39,720
He deserved to be scolded.

178
00:10:39,720 --> 00:10:40,670
Cheng Miaomiao!

179
00:10:42,550 --> 00:10:44,030
Can you stop bullying Li Si?

180
00:10:44,030 --> 00:10:44,550
Don't you know

181
00:10:44,550 --> 00:10:45,120
how good Li Si has been to you

182
00:10:45,120 --> 00:10:46,270
all these years?

183
00:10:48,200 --> 00:10:49,910
He's such a good kid.

184
00:10:52,080 --> 00:10:53,940
Can't you be a little nicer to him?

185
00:10:55,630 --> 00:10:57,630
Wait, what did I say?

186
00:10:57,630 --> 00:10:58,000
And you just

187
00:10:58,000 --> 00:10:59,550
gave me a good scolding.

188
00:11:00,390 --> 00:11:01,550
Your mom means...

189
00:11:02,030 --> 00:11:02,840
Well...

190
00:11:03,360 --> 00:11:04,240
Well, you're about to

191
00:11:04,240 --> 00:11:05,630
start 12th grade, right?

192
00:11:05,630 --> 00:11:06,750
After that, you'll have to take the college entrance exams.

193
00:11:06,750 --> 00:11:08,680
Then you two will have to part ways.

194
00:11:09,510 --> 00:11:10,720
You should

195
00:11:10,720 --> 00:11:11,150
b-b-both

196
00:11:11,150 --> 00:11:13,280
treat each other better while you can.

197
00:11:14,120 --> 00:11:16,030
We won't be apart.

198
00:11:16,030 --> 00:11:17,550
He'll go wherever I go.

199
00:11:17,910 --> 00:11:19,150
We have a deal.

200
00:11:27,550 --> 00:11:28,200
It's not like he's had this disease

201
00:11:28,200 --> 00:11:29,840
for just a day or two.

202
00:11:31,550 --> 00:11:33,440
But I didn't notice anything.

203
00:11:33,440 --> 00:11:35,630
What kind of mother am I?

204
00:11:35,630 --> 00:11:37,960
I've failed my son.

205
00:11:40,320 --> 00:11:41,600
I'm a terrible father.

206
00:11:45,000 --> 00:11:45,960
I deserve to die.

207
00:11:46,390 --> 00:11:48,050
Stop saying things like that.

208
00:12:14,510 --> 00:12:16,070
Mom, I'm going to school.

209
00:12:18,150 --> 00:12:19,950
Why haven't you gone to work yet?

210
00:12:20,240 --> 00:12:21,440
To take you to school.

211
00:12:22,320 --> 00:12:23,720
Take me? Why?

212
00:12:24,240 --> 00:12:25,360
Why what?

213
00:12:25,360 --> 00:12:26,160
It's on my way.

214
00:12:26,440 --> 00:12:27,440
I happen to have something to do near your school.

215
00:12:27,440 --> 00:12:28,240
Son,

216
00:12:28,790 --> 00:12:30,190
let us take you to school.

217
00:12:30,910 --> 00:12:31,720
What?

218
00:12:32,080 --> 00:12:33,360
I've long said that, given my temperament,

219
00:12:33,360 --> 00:12:34,000
I deserve the lifestyle

220
00:12:34,000 --> 00:12:35,790
of a young master traveling in a private car.

221
00:12:35,790 --> 00:12:37,320
We can take Miaomiao with us

222
00:12:37,320 --> 00:12:39,320
so that she can ride on my coattails.

223
00:12:40,120 --> 00:12:41,120
Let's go.

224
00:12:52,440 --> 00:12:54,240
Mom, what's for dinner tonight?

225
00:12:56,200 --> 00:12:57,440
You're all here.

226
00:12:58,320 --> 00:12:58,790
Go. Go.

227
00:12:58,790 --> 00:13:00,480
You go to Xiaoshudu Restaurant for dinner.

228
00:13:00,480 --> 00:13:03,010
We're discussing something important here.

229
00:13:03,390 --> 00:13:04,870
Discussing a wedding, right?

230
00:13:04,870 --> 00:13:06,360
Why didn't you include me?

231
00:13:07,150 --> 00:13:07,870
Why isn't my grandma here?

232
00:13:07,870 --> 00:13:08,960
Why are you so nosy?

233
00:13:08,960 --> 00:13:10,080
Go already.

234
00:13:10,440 --> 00:13:11,870
Yaya's already there.

235
00:13:11,870 --> 00:13:12,760
Hurry up and go to eat,

236
00:13:12,760 --> 00:13:14,020
then do your homework.

237
00:13:14,550 --> 00:13:15,150
Well...

238
00:13:37,150 --> 00:13:40,150
Why don't we take Li Si to see a traditional Chinese medicine doctor?

239
00:13:40,150 --> 00:13:43,480
I heard that traditional Chinese medicine can cure cancer.

240
00:14:15,480 --> 00:14:16,480
Hu,

241
00:14:17,270 --> 00:14:18,550
stop crying.

242
00:14:24,120 --> 00:14:26,050
No one's allowed to be sad anymore.

243
00:14:26,750 --> 00:14:27,630
None of us...

244
00:14:30,080 --> 00:14:31,550
should tell Li Si about it.

245
00:14:31,870 --> 00:14:32,910
We have to make him

246
00:14:33,320 --> 00:14:35,630
stay happy during this time.

247
00:14:35,630 --> 00:14:37,320
We have to protect Li Si.

248
00:14:44,870 --> 00:14:45,870
Honey, do you remember?

249
00:14:45,870 --> 00:14:48,130
Don't you remember what the doctor said?

250
00:14:50,750 --> 00:14:52,150
He said that a stable mood

251
00:14:52,150 --> 00:14:55,480
is the key to fighting cancer cells.

252
00:14:58,870 --> 00:15:00,870
We're like undercover agents now.

253
00:15:04,240 --> 00:15:05,970
We can't let anything slip out.

254
00:15:07,150 --> 00:15:08,410
This is a tough battle.

255
00:15:08,840 --> 00:15:09,960
We have to win it,

256
00:15:11,270 --> 00:15:12,080
okay?

257
00:15:16,600 --> 00:15:19,840
Why is this happening to me?

258
00:15:19,840 --> 00:15:21,510
What should we do?

259
00:15:36,120 --> 00:15:37,870
If anyone messes this up,

260
00:15:42,240 --> 00:15:44,120
I'll never speak to them again.

261
00:16:22,720 --> 00:16:23,510
Ling,

262
00:16:24,200 --> 00:16:25,120
are you sure

263
00:16:25,320 --> 00:16:27,120
you want to sell the restaurant?

264
00:16:34,750 --> 00:16:36,550
I'm not sure yet if it's enough.

265
00:16:39,670 --> 00:16:40,870
I'll look for a buyer.

266
00:16:41,390 --> 00:16:43,120
I'm sure we can get a good price.

267
00:16:54,360 --> 00:16:55,670
Who did it?

268
00:16:59,240 --> 00:17:00,550
Me!

269
00:17:06,240 --> 00:17:08,200
Director Xiao, I'm sorry.

270
00:17:08,400 --> 00:17:10,240
I'll be more careful next time.

271
00:17:21,480 --> 00:17:22,200
Director.

272
00:17:28,310 --> 00:17:29,160
What happened

273
00:17:29,160 --> 00:17:30,640
to your uniform?

274
00:17:31,960 --> 00:17:34,200
See? It's all wrinkled.

275
00:17:35,310 --> 00:17:36,970
You're a sprightly young man.

276
00:17:40,640 --> 00:17:42,300
Your hair is getting long too.

277
00:17:42,640 --> 00:17:43,680
Go get it trimmed.

278
00:17:45,880 --> 00:17:46,750
Got it?

279
00:17:47,640 --> 00:17:48,510
Yes, Director.

280
00:17:54,240 --> 00:17:54,830
Be careful

281
00:17:54,830 --> 00:17:56,830
playing in the hallway. Don't fall.

282
00:18:12,510 --> 00:18:14,640
Being in a relationship sure changes people.

283
00:18:14,640 --> 00:18:16,500
She's become so much gentler now.

284
00:18:16,790 --> 00:18:18,440
Come on, Xiaowa.

285
00:18:18,440 --> 00:18:19,240
Let's continue to play.

286
00:18:19,240 --> 00:18:20,110
I'll pick it up.

287
00:18:20,720 --> 00:18:21,510
Hurry.

288
00:18:23,030 --> 00:18:25,160
Let's play, Si.

289
00:18:25,750 --> 00:18:27,160
Let me say it upfront.

